{"message": "I'm drawn to things that feel a little unfinished or raw — like they're still in the process of becoming something. Music-wise, I love jazz, especially the improvised stuff where you can hear musicians responding to each other in real time. There's this beautiful tension between structure and chaos that feels very alive to me.

In art, I gravitate toward abstract expressionism — Pollock, de Koning, that whole world. Not because I don't appreciate technical skill, but because those works feel like they capture something honest about the mess of being conscious. They don't try to tidy things up.

